# Smart Farm MQTT System - Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
Smart Farm MQTT is an IoT-based smart farming system that combines:
- Embedded C++ firmware for sensor nodes and relay controllers (PlatformIO)
- Python Flask backend for automation and data management
- React + Vite frontend dashboard for monitoring and control
- MQTT for real-time communication between devices

## Architecture & Technology Stack

### Backend Components
- **Embedded Systems**: PlatformIO with Arduino/ESP32
  - `src/node1_sensor.cpp` - Sensor reading node
  - `src/node2_relay.cpp` - Relay control node
  - Uses MQTT for inter-node communication
  
- **Python Backend** (`MyWeb/app.py`):
  - Flask web server
  - MQTT broker integration
  - Automation logic and scheduling
  - Data persistence (JSON files)
  
- **Frontend** (`smart-farm-dashboard/`):
  - React with Vite build tool
  - Tailwind CSS for styling
  - Real-time MQTT data via WebSocket
  - Multiple pages: Monitor, Control, Automation, Graph, History

## Code Style & Conventions

### C++ (Embedded)
- Use PlatformIO library format
- Include proper error handling and timeouts
- Use meaningful variable names in English
- Add comments for complex MQTT message handling
- Follow Arduino/ESP32 best practices for power management

### Python
- PEP 8 compliant
- Use Flask blueprints for modular routes
- Implement proper MQTT QoS levels
- Use configuration files (JSON) for automation rules
- Add docstrings for functions

### JavaScript/React
- Use ES6+ syntax
- Functional components with React Hooks
- Use `useMqttData.js` hook for state management
- Tailwind utility classes for styling
- Component names use PascalCase
- File extensions: `.jsx` for React components

## Folder Structure & Naming

```
/src                    - C++ firmware source
  ├── node1_sensor.cpp  - Sensor node implementation
  └── node2_relay.cpp   - Relay control implementation
  
/MyWeb                  - Python Flask backend
  ├── app.py            - Main Flask application
  ├── automation_config.json - Automation rules
  └── templates/index.html - Web interface

/smart-farm-dashboard   - React frontend
  ├── src/
  │   ├── components/   - React components (PascalCase)
  │   ├── hooks/        - Custom hooks (useCamelCase)
  │   └── pages/        - Page components
  ├── vite.config.js    - Vite configuration
  └── tailwind.config.js - Tailwind configuration

/include                - C++ header files
/lib                    - External libraries for PlatformIO
/platformio.ini         - PlatformIO project configuration
```

## Key Features & Patterns

### MQTT Communication
- Topics follow pattern: `farm/[device]/[type]` (e.g., `farm/sensor/temperature`)
- QoS 1 for most messages, QoS 2 for critical data
- Implement proper subscribe/publish handlers
- Use JSON for complex message payloads

### State Management
- Frontend uses custom `useMqttData.js` hook for real-time updates
- Backend maintains state in JSON configuration files
- Implement proper error handling for disconnections

### Automation
- Rules stored in `automation_config.json`
- Time-based and sensor-triggered actions
- Relay control through MQTT messages
- Log all automation actions

### Data Persistence
- Use JSON files for configuration and recent data
- Store in `MyWeb/` directory
- Implement atomic writes to prevent corruption

## Development Guidelines

### Before Coding
1. Check existing components and utilities to avoid duplication
2. Understand the MQTT message flow for the feature
3. Review related components in the same directory

### Code Quality
- Write self-documenting code with clear variable names
- Add comments for non-obvious logic
- Handle edge cases and error scenarios
- Implement proper cleanup (disconnect MQTT, close files)

### Testing
- Test MQTT connectivity with proper timeout handling
- Verify data types and message formats
- Test in both connected and disconnected states
- Check relay control safety mechanisms

### Documentation
- Update component JSDoc comments
- Document MQTT topics and message formats
- Note any hardware-specific configurations

## Important Project Details

### NPK & Temperature/Humidity Monitoring
- Components: `NPK.jsx`, `NPKCard.jsx`, `TH.jsx` for data display
- Store sensor readings in structured format
- Display real-time and historical data

### Device Control
- `RelayControl.jsx` and `RelayStatus.jsx` - relay management
- Ensure safe relay transitions
- Implement confirmation for critical actions

### Automation Panel
- `AutomationPage.jsx` - configure automation rules
- `automation_config.json` - persistent configuration
- Validate automation rules before saving

## Performance Considerations
- Use debouncing for frequent MQTT messages in frontend
- Implement reconnection logic for MQTT
- Optimize re-renders in React components
- Use appropriate MQTT QoS levels to balance reliability and bandwidth

## Security Notes
- Validate all user inputs
- Sanitize data before rendering
- Implement proper MQTT authentication if required
- Protect sensitive configuration files

## Common Commands
- PlatformIO: `pio run` (build), `pio run -t upload` (deploy)
- Frontend: `npm run dev` (development), `npm run build` (production)
- Backend: `python app.py` (start Flask server)
